<body>
	
<header>
	Look at the following statements about the speaking exam and decide whether they are true or false.
</header>
	
<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../Media/ED_SP_002.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><br/><ol id="questionList"><br/><li id="1">You will have to talk about yourself.<a id="q1" >True</a><tab/><a id="q2" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="2">The Examiner will ask you to call him or her Mr/Ms X.<a id="q3" >True</a><tab/><a id="q4" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="3">You need to have a lot of information about a lot of topics.<a id="q5" >True</a><tab/><a id="q6" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="4">The Examiner will ask all the questions.<a id="q7" >True</a><tab/><a id="q8" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="5">The interview time will vary a little from candidate to candidate.<a id="q9" >True</a><tab/><a id="q10" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="6">You can ask about your marks.<a id="q11" >True</a><tab/><a id="q12" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="7">The Examiner may judge you partly on your appearance.<a id="q13" >True</a><tab/><a id="q14" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="8">The Examiner will ask where you are from.<a id="q15" >True</a><tab/><a id="q16" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="9">Giving examples to support your opinion will help you do better.<a id="q17" >True</a><tab/><a id="q18" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="10">The discussion topic will be chosen by the Examiner.<a id="q19" >True</a><tab/><a id="q20" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="11">You are required to have definite opinions.<a id="q21" >True</a><tab/><a id="q22" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="12">You must communicate, no matter what topic is presented.<a id="q23" >True</a><tab/><a id="q24" >False</a><br/></li></ol>
</section>
<section id="fb1">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">1. You will probably be asked about what you do and where you are from.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb2">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">2. Examiners will give you their full name and will not ask you to call them anything.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb3">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">3. This test is about communication not knowledge. </font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb4">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">4. You can ask examiners to repeat a question but you shouldn't ask them anything else.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb5">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">5. The exam is between 11 and 14 minutes.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb6">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">6. You will find out how well you did when you get your exam results, no sooner!</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb7">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">7. Looking nice helps with the impression you give but the examiner is there to mark your communication.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb8">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">8. It is a good idea to give some extra information as the examiner may not know your country very well.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb9">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">9. Giving examples and explanations is always a good idea.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb10">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">10. Examiners have several topics to choose from.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb11">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">11. You are only expected to communicate your thoughts, not have definite opinions. </font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb12">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">12. You should do your best with whichever topic you get.</font></p>
</section>
